        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 24 at 5:23PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 523 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 5 miles east of Edgewood to 9 miles
north of Mountainair, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Moriarty, Estancia, Edgewood, Willard, McIntosh, Chilili, Tajique,
Stanley, Cedar Grove and Torreon.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 40 between Mile Markers 187 and 209.
Highway 60 between Mile Markers 210 and 222.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Heavy rains from severe thunderstorms can produce sudden and
dangerous flows in arroyos, ditches and over low water crossings. Do
not attempt to drive through areas where water covers the roadway.</instruction>
